    menu:
        "Ask for legal guarantees in writing now":
            "You lean across the table and request explicit contractual clauses ensuring community stewardship and oversight committees with binding seats. Your voice is clipped; you signal Ishaan to pull up draft language."
        "Ask for time to consult the community":
            "You breathe, forcing the meeting's heat into a different rhythm. 'I need time,' you say. 'I need to bring this to Luka, to Kaito, to the nursery hands. I can't sign a future for people I haven't heard from.'"

    # --- merge ---
    "..."
    "Elena Moro's jaw tightens in a way that is almost human."

    elena_moro "We are on a timetable. Federal grants, procurement windows — these are not indefinite. If you attempt to stall for months, the opportunity costs are significant. We can't afford to wait while another storm unthreads the whole coastline."
    "You can hear the agency's calendar like a threat. It is a practical knife, and it presses against urgency. The room's air shifts; the rain sounds like a drumbeat in time with the urgency. Your throat"
    "works. The obligation you feel — to the town, to remediate past errors, to prevent loss — is a pressure cooker waiting to open."
    hide elena_moro
    show marin_alvarez at left:
        zoom 0.7

    marin_alvarez "If we move quickly without safeguards, history repeats. If we stall, people may lose everything now. There is no clean path."
    hide maya_chen
    show elena_moro at right:
        zoom 0.7

    elena_moro "There's a smart path. You know the stakes, Marin. You know how to translate science into something people can accept. Join us formally. Take the funding, lead the mitigation, let us manage the risky operations. We'll build faster than any loose network of workshops."
    "Her offer is surgical: join us, accept the agency's terms, and you become the bridge between a machine that moves quickly and a people who have lived on a different clock. It is an offer of agency and constraint folded into one."
    "Luka's eyes find yours, and for the first time in the meeting his voice is fatigue-strangled."
    hide ishaan_rao
    show luka_sorensen at center:
        zoom 0.7

    luka_sorensen "There are things money can't rebuild. Names on a dock, the taste of salt on bread made from harbor-sown grains. Decide if you are buying time or selling memory."
    "You feel the room constrict to the size of the table. Your hands curl. The seashell at your throat — warm against skin — feels like a relic and a question both. The storm outside hammers as if pressing an exclamation into your chest."
    "Your mind runs through consequences in fast cuts: children who rely on the floating farm, elders who maintain tidal songs, the coral nursery frames that need delicate tending, and the iron certainty of a concrete barrier."
    "You count lives and marshes in the same breath and fail to make either fit."
    "Kaito Sakamura's look is unreadable, heavy with accusation without words you can parse. Maya's impatience is a live wire. Ishaan's calmness is a sluice gate waiting to close. Elena Moro's offer gleams like a way forward and a closing door."
    "Your pulse throbs in an accelerating rhythm. The room's lights seem to dim and sharpen at once. You can feel the arousal rising — the negotiating tempo turning into pressure, the room narrowing to the single axis of choice. For a breath you are a tide pulled between two banks."

    marin_alvarez "You promised to protect. To whom are you accountable? To the people who will lose gardens and rites? Or to the larger number who will have roofs when the worst comes?"
    "You put your hand to the table, feeling the grain under your palm — a human texture in an engineered plan. The shell at your throat presses into your collarbone as if asking you to play the next note of the town's song."

    elena_moro "Marin, we're offering you leadership with resources. We're asking for operational deference in certain zones. Say yes, and we begin construction. Say no, and we walk away to other sites. You know our reach. The window closes."
    "You sense the climax fold in on itself. The air is electric with consequence. Your voice comes out small."

    marin_alvarez "If I accept, I become the face of a choice that will take things from people in the name of protection."

    elena_moro "Then be the one to remake that choice so it is as equitable as possible. Your presence matters."
    "Your chest tightens with a pressure that is nearly pain. The storm outside crescendos — a sudden slap of wind knocks a stack of pamphlets off a side table, papers skittering like small white fish. Someone curses under their breath. The room surges with a single, shared intake of breath."
    "Your internal monologue runs rapid and sharp now: guilt for earlier projects, the memory of the marsh you helped redraw, Luka's maps annotated in shaky ink, Maya's pleading face. This is not just policy. This is moral scalpel work under time."
    "You look at the holographic map of the Promenade — a bright line where a hand-drawn mosaic once lived. The thought of those mosaics disappearing, replaced by engineered panels, is a small death."
    "You feel your fingers brush the seashell at your throat. Your pulse is a drum. Decision waits like a held fist."
    hide marin_alvarez
    hide elena_moro
    hide luka_sorensen

    scene bg ch9_453e40_2 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Rain reaches a high, insistent pitch; a distant siren doppler-fades then steadies]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Electronic pulse tightens into a serrated string]
    "You inhale, the breath a thin wire."
    show marin_alvarez at left:
        zoom 0.7

    marin_alvarez "This is the moment I chose Elena for. This is the moment I test whether I can keep my hands from repeating the past. It is also the moment when compromise smells dangerously like surrender."
    "The room is a pressure chamber. Elena Moro's offer sits incandescent and cold between you. Your options arrange themselves like a map you must cross."
    "You close your eyes for half a second to steady the tremor in your fingers. When you open them, the tableau is the same, but everything is louder — Luka's soft warning; Kaito Sakamura's unreadable tide; Maya's impatience; Ishaan's composed gravity; Elena Moro's quiet insistence."
    "You have to decide what to do with the authority they've handed you. The choice will ripple outward, reshaping more than shoreline."
    hide marin_alvarez

    scene bg ch9_453e40_3 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Holds a single unresolved chord — expectant, taut]
    "You sense the window of time Elena keeps pressing. The room waits."
